     <p>Some of our websites also carry embedded 'share' buttons to enable users  of the site to easily share articles with their peers through a number  of popular social networks. These sites may set a cookie when you are  also logged in to or otherwise using their service. </p>
     <h3>YouTube cookies - set using Privacy Enhanced Mode</h3>
     <p>On some pages we embed videos from our official YouTube channel using YouTube's   privacy-enhanced mode. This mode may set cookies on your computer once   you click on the YouTube video player, but YouTube will not store   personally-identifiable cookie information for playbacks of embedded   videos using the privacy-enhanced mode. To find out more please visit <a title="External link" href="http://www.google.com/support/youtube/bin/answer.py?hl=en-GB&amp;answer=171780" target="_blank">YouTube's embedding videos information page</a>.</p>
     <h3>S7 'Add This' cookies</h3>
     <p>On some of our pages we provide our users with a tool from AddThis <a href="http://www.addthis.com/">http://www.addthis.com/</a> . This service allows users to share our page content with other people via many different social networking sites. By default this service uses cookies, however we have disabled the use of cookies for AddThis on most of our pages following the information provided by the AddThis support team. The cookie set by the AddThis service is called '__atuvc'. </p>
     <h3>Accessibility toolbar cookies</h3>
     <p>On some of our sites we have additional accessibility tools installed. These set cookies called 'fontSize' and 'pageStyle_BUACCESSCENTRE'. These are essential for the operation of those parts of the site and are removed when   you close you browser. No personal information is stored by these cookies.</p>
